      "content": "but \"surviving the journey\" just sounds like prolonging the inevitable. if the destination is just destruction, why is the journey even worth it? it feels more rational to just opt out now rather than waiting around to watch everything decay and suffer through the collapse. doesn't it seem more logical to just leave early if you know there's no meaningful future left?",
